(92879, 216719, 8107, 1, 'Awakening#1 (smog)', '', '2014-12-02 00:00:00', 2014, 19, 1, 1, 'Are we there yet? \nNo \n\nWhat’s the day \nWhat’s the time \n\nDeadly silence \nSmokey skies \n\nHell broke loose \nThe crowd goes wild \n\nWaxy faces \nEyes grow wide \n\nHis body is his armour \nSo frail and so thin \nThey push and shove and beat and poke but still they cannot win \n\n***********************Chorus\n(I’ll rip you to pieces) \nYou break my fingers\n(You rip me to pieces) \nYou break my bones\n(I’ll rip you to pieces) \nYou pull the trigger\n(You rip me to pieces) \nOur dear protector \n\n(I’ll rip you to pieces) \nYour ugly grimace \n(You rip me to pieces) \nYour evil sneer \n(I’ll rip you to pieces) \nWe flirt with madness \n(You rip me to pieces) \nThe end is near***********************\n\n\nThere''s no hope   No redemption\n(Crack   Crack my skull)\nMother please don''t cry   There''s is a better world for us out there\nCan you see it?   Or is it just me?\n(And you’ll be pleased   And you’ll be pleased)\n\nA vague sense of unease that the gruesome climax of my life  \n(Crack   Crack my skull)\nWas being rehearsed years in advance\n(In the name of peace    In the name of peace)\n\nBe my friend walk me out of this plight\n(Crack   Crack   Crack my skull)\nWalking along the sea I see the tents and the people they''re all…   They''re all smiling at me\n(And I’m released   And I’m released)\n\nOut of nowhere we became the traitor\n(Crack my skull   Crack   Crack my skull)\nThis is an army with no clear leader\n(And make me the beast    And make me the beast)\n\n\n**Chorus**', '', 184, '', '', '', '', 'david boring', '', 0, 1, 0, '2014-12-03 00:23:29', '2015-03-12 14:17:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
